Homa Bay County will for the first time host the National Beach Tour. This is in conjunction with Kenya Volleyball Federation. The event is set to take place between October 23 and 24 at Victoria Sands Beach Hotel and Mbita Tourist Beach Hotel. The participating teams will be expected to register three pairs per gender and will be expected to cover their own traveling costs and upkeep and should confirm participation by October 18 According to the chairman of the Beach Volleyball Commission Moses Mbuthia, the competition is open to teams even from across the borders ‘’We have written an open invitation and all teams including those from across the borders are welcome to participate. Those willing should confirm participation by close of business October 18,’’ explained Mbuthia. Homabay will just be the first county to host the circuit which will go through to all the 47 counties in the country. Mbuthia admitted the game is still in the infancy stage in the country but is optimistic about its growth. Also Read: ‘’We want to ‘market’ the beach volleyball in all counties and already there are some counties well-endowed with sand,’’ added Mbuthia. Kenya’s pair of Gaudencia Makokha and Brackcides Agala finished last in group ‘D’ of the Tokyo Olympic Games that had Brazil, USA, and Lativa. ‘’The County government of Homa Bay has already said they are ready to partner with us and thus we are headed there.’’ Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam